# Grammar + editor build artifacts. Committed grammar files
# (grammars/textmate/iron.tmLanguage.json and grammars/tree-sitter/iron/grammar.js)
# are drift-gated, so they stay tracked; only transient build outputs and
# per-editor node_modules/target are ignored. Note: tree-sitter's own
# src/parser.c is generated by `tree-sitter generate` — we commit only
# grammar.js + queries/.
editors/**/node_modules/
editors/vscode/out/
editors/vscode/dist/
# Grammar copies are generated by editors/vscode/prepackage.mjs from the
# drift-guarded sources under grammars/textmate/. They are regenerated at
# every `npm run package`.
editors/vscode/syntaxes/iron.tmLanguage.json
editors/vscode/language-configuration.json
# Local .vsix output from `vsce package` + Electron test cache directory
# pulled by @vscode/test-electron on first run.
editors/vscode/*.vsix
editors/vscode/.vscode-test/
editors/zed/target/
grammars/tree-sitter/iron/build/
grammars/tree-sitter/iron/node_modules/
grammars/tree-sitter/iron/package-lock.json
grammars/tree-sitter/iron/src/parser.c
grammars/tree-sitter/iron/src/node-types.json
grammars/tree-sitter/iron/src/grammar.json
grammars/tree-sitter/iron/src/tree_sitter/
grammars/tree-sitter/iron/bindings/node/
# iron.wasm is produced by `tree-sitter build --wasm`; CI builds + uploads
# it as an artifact and attaches it to GitHub Releases.
grammars/tree-sitter/iron/iron.wasm
tests/grammars/**/node_modules/
tests/grammars/**/package-lock.json

# iron build writes iron.lock alongside iron.toml in package roots. It's a
# regenerated build artifact, never a source file. Used by
# tests/integration/lib_consume/<consumer>/ on every test run.
iron.lock
target/
